[normal]Written evidence [bold]from Sense About Science (GMC0021)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Executive summary: [bold]We believe that the 
[normal]General Medical Council
[normal] should have a role in ensuring that doctors work
[normal]ing on clinical trials or who worked on a clinical trial in the past on any treatment in current use ensures that the clinical trial has been registered and a summary of the findings is publicly available. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“(i) Selective non-publication of unflattering trial data is research misconduct; 
[normal]“(ii) Registered medical practitioners who give grounds to believe they h
[normal]ave been involved in such conduct should have their fitness to practice assessed by the GMC.” 
